{
	"info": {
		"_postman_id": "auth-service-tienda-generica",
		"name": "Auth Service — Tienda Genérica",
		"description": "# Auth Service API Documentation\n\n## Overview\nThe **auth-service** is a stateless Go microservice (port **3001**) responsible for authenticating system users (employees/administrators) and issuing JWTs. It has **no database** of its own — it delegates user lookup to **user-service** via internal HTTP calls.\n\n## Architecture\n```\nHandler → HTTP Client → user-service (Clean Architecture, no DB layer)\n```\n\n## Authentication Flow\n1. Client sends `POST /login` with `username` and `password`\n2. auth-service calls `GET {USER_SERVICE_URL}/users/by-username/{username}` with `X-Internal: true`\n3. If user exists and is active, password is verified against the bcrypt hash\n4. On success, a signed **HS256 JWT** (24h expiry) is returned\n\n## JWT Payload\n```json\n{\n  \"user_id\": \"<cedula>\",\n  \"username\": \"<username>\",\n  \"iat\": <unix_timestamp>,\n  \"exp\": <unix_timestamp + 24h>\n}\n```\n\n## Standard Response Envelope\nEvery endpoint returns this structure:\n```json\n{\n  \"success\": true | false,\n  \"data\": { ... } | null,\n  \"error\": null | \"Descriptive error message\"\n}\n```\n\n## Error Scenarios\n| Scenario | Status | Error Message |\n|---|---|---|\n| Missing username or password | 400 | `username y password son requeridos` |\n| User not found | 401 | `Credenciales inválidas` |\n| Wrong password | 401 | `Credenciales inválidas` |\n| Inactive user | 401 | `Usuario inactivo` |\n| user-service unreachable | 500 | `Error al consultar el servicio de usuarios` |\n\n## Dependencies\n- **user-service** (port 3002) must be running for login to work\n- Requires `JWT_SECRET` environment variable for token signing",
		"schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
	},
