						"description": "## Login — Successful Authentication\n\nAuthenticates a system user with valid credentials and returns a JWT.\n\n### Prerequisites\n- **user-service** must be running on port 3002\n- The user `admininicial` must exist (auto-seeded on first startup of user-service)\n\n### Request Body\n| Field | Type | Required | Description |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| username | string | Yes | Username of the system user |\n| password | string | Yes | Plain-text password |\n\n### Response\n- **200 OK** — Authentication successful, JWT returned in `data.token`\n\n### Notes\n- The returned JWT is valid for **24 hours**\n- JWT payload contains `user_id` (cédula) and `username`\n- The token is automatically saved to the `auth_token` collection variable for use in subsequent requests"
					},
